# ttt-bot Conventions

A custom Discord bot for Tiny Temptation Tubs (TTT).

## General

- Keep secrets (bot tokens, API keys) out of source. Use a `.env` file loaded at runtime; never hardcode credentials.
- Prefer small, focused modules: one command/handler per file.
- Use async/await; always handle rejected promises and log failures with context.

## Discord Interactions

- Acknowledge interactions promptly (defer if work takes >3s) to avoid "interaction failed".
- Validate user input and permissions before performing privileged actions.
- Fail gracefully: reply to the user with a clear message instead of letting the handler throw.
